article.headline: Duke Deen scores 16 in Bradley's 76-60 victory over Northern Illinois
article.description: — Duke Deen's 16 points helped Bradley defeat Northern Illinois 76-60 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Duke Deen scores 16 in Bradley's 76-60 victory over Northern Illinois
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- — Duke Deen's 16 points helped Bradley defeat Northern Illinois 76-60 on Saturday night. Deen also added five rebounds and five assists for the Braves (3-1). Darius Hannah finished 7 of 9 from the floor to add 15 points. Zek Montgomery had 13 points and shot 4 of 7 from the field and 3 for 3 from the line. The Huskies (2-2) were led by Quentin Jones, who recorded 19 points, two steals and three blocks. Ethan Butler added 15 points and Nasir Muhammad scored nine. Bradley took the lead with 6:49 remaining in the first half and never looked back. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
